5.3.2 Unless prohibited by a Government Authority or Applicable Law, Valeant shall be notified promptly by Dova upon receipt of any notice of inspection or investigation by a Governmental Authority concerning matters potentially affecting the Valeant Activities. In such instances, Dova's obligations will include:

(i) maintaining regular communication with Valeant about the progress and status of the inspection or investigation;
(ii) sharing in writing with Valeant any assertions, findings, and related results from the Governmental Authorities regarding the Product or its promotion that emerge during the inspection or investigation;
(iii) disclosing to Valeant all actions taken or proposed to be taken under this Section 5.3.2 in relation to the Valeant Activities before their execution; and
(iv) collaborating with Valeant to modify any aspect of the Valeant Activities, should findings or Governmental Authority recommendations suggest such changes. However, it is important to note that Valeant will not be obligated to engage in any Valeant Activities if a finding or Government Authority has requested or suggested that Valeant may not undertake such activity. The onus remains on Valeant to decide whether to comply with the suggested modifications or discontinue the relevant activities, as deemed appropriate.
